.TH "domain_dirty_limits" 9 "domain_dirty_limits" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
domain_dirty_limits \- calculate thresh and bg_thresh for a wb_domain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" domain_dirty_limits
.BI "(struct dirty_throttle_control *dtc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dtc" 12
dirty_throttle_control of interest
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calculate \fIdtc->thresh\fP and ->bg_thresh considering
vm_dirty_{bytes|ratio} and dirty_background_{bytes|ratio}.  The caller
must ensure that \fIdtc->avail\fP is set before calling this function.  The
dirty limits will be lifted by 1/4 for real-time tasks.
